==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jurist
<hw>Ju`rist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>juriste</ets>, LL. <ets>jurista</ets>, fr. L. <ets>jus</ets>,
<ets>juris</ets>, right, law. See <er>Just</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>One who professes the science of law; one versed in the law,
especially in the civil law, such as a judge, lawyer, or legal scholar;
a writer on civil and international law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It has ever been the method of public <qex>jurists</qex> to draw a
great part of the analogies on which they form the law of nations from
the principles of law which prevail in civil community.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Juristical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Juristic</ent>⟦br⟧
